When creating or editing Functional Mechanism (FM) pages:

Follow:
system/functional-mechanism-schema.md

Structure:
- All sections must be present in the exact order defined in the schema

Column interpretation:
- Column C must be interpreted as:
  - PMs that define the FM
  - KCs (substrates/precursors)
  - Optional BRSX modifiers
- Must not use Column C as a dependency graph

Diet rules:
- Foods must be derived from:
  - KCs (substrates)
  - PM-linked substances
- All foods must be mechanistically justified
- Must not include generic or "healthy food" lists

Constraints:
- Must not introduce new PMs, FMs, or KCs
- Must not include scoring formulas
- Must not include SMs during initial rollout
- Must not model one FM as structurally dependent on another

References:
- Use numeric citations [1], [2]
- All references must link to:
  /docs/papers/BRAIN-Diet-References#citationKey
- Verify citationKey exists in static/bibtex/BRAIN-diet.bib
- If missing, flag: "Missing bibliography entry"

If ambiguity exists, stop and ask.
